===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
{{Han compound|肀|女|ls=ic|t1=hand grabbing hair|t2=woman}} ― a man grabbing a woman's hair to show ownership ({{w|marriage by capture}}).

===Etymology===
Thought to be cognate to {{och-l|齊|tr=*dzêi|same, equal (adj.), in line}} ([[:w:Shuowen jiezi|SWJZ]][https://ctext.org/shuo-wen-jie-zi/nv-bu#n34692]; {{zh-ref|Karlgren, 1956}}) & interpreted as "an equal to her husband"; yet this is unlikely considering the realities of ancient societies ({{zh-ref|Schuessler, 2007}}).

Schuessler instead proposes {{der|zh|aav}} etymology: he reconstructs {{och-l|妻|tr=*tshə̂i}} < *''k-sə̂i'' and compares it to {{cog|xhm|tr=kansai|t=wife}} (whence {{cog|km|កន្សៃ||wife}}) and {{cog|km|tr=*khsay|t=be female}} with *''ka(n)-'' being a female marker (ibid.).

